    "According to Cohen (1988), Pearson correlation coefficients above 0.80 indicate strong reliability.",
    "Additionally, Koo and Li (2016) suggest that ICC values above 0.75 denote good reliability, supporting this study's findings.",
    "CFA was conducted to test the three-factor structure obtained from the EFA.",
